# Architecture Manual Maintenance Rule

Use `doc/architecture-manual.qmd` as the source of truth for architecture structure/boundaries.
Use `doc/architecture-adr-manual.qmd` as the source of truth for architecture decisions (ADRs).

## End-of-step checklist (run before completing any substantial work step)

- Check whether changed files affect architecture, boundaries, runtime behavior, delivery, or security posture.
- If yes, update `doc/architecture-manual.qmd` in the same step:
  - Update "Last updated" date.
  - Update delivery/build paths if commands changed.
  - Update full-client vs reduced app-profile boundaries if capabilities changed.
  - Update constraints if new rules emerged.
- If decision rationale changed or a new architectural decision was made, update `doc/architecture-adr-manual.qmd` in the same step.
- Verify architecture consistency for both targets:
  - Full browser fat-client path still valid.
  - Reduced app-profile path still valid.
- If no architecture impact, explicitly confirm that no manual update is required.

## Documentation discipline

- Keep ADR entries concise, dated, and status-marked in `doc/architecture-adr-manual.qmd`.
- Prefer additive updates over silent rewrites so historical intent stays visible.
